Costco thank you for the kind and sweet thoughts to allow first responders front line access during this crisis.
However, my husband and many others with badges would never feel comfortable cutting the line... just to pull out their badge and make everyone else wait even longer for their essential items.

My husband is already in public enough and has enough worries of bringing it home to our 5 month old daughter!
Sincerely,
A Fire family with an infant.

snippet.textDisplay:
Why Doesn't Costco improve its online store? Costco lags Amazon too far behind. The number of items Costco sells is way too limited with way too many to be purchased at the store. In addition, Costco charges way too much for the delivery. Not only the item is about 35% more expensive online but also there is an extra shipping cost.
I understand that Costco does not have the infrastructure that Amazon put in place but they should think out of the box to catch up. For example, an intermediate step that Costco can easily implement is to order online for drive-through pick up. Customers can place their orders online for later pick up. Their packages should already be prepared and boxed by Costco workers. It should give an extra boost to the Costco business.

snippet.textDisplay: My husband and I are costco card holders and seniors with compromised immune systems who live in rural Nova Scotia so have not gone in here since this virus all started. We do use their pharmacy though as their dispensing fee is a whole lot cheaper than the average drug store but that is not the only reason. If you have your doctor fax your prescriptions to them they will fill them, charge your credit card and mail them out to you within a day or two and there is no charge for this service. We have done this for a while now and it is great. The only thing they don’t mail out is insulin or narcotics so we get those at our local pharmacy and have a friend pick them up for us and deliver them to our mail box outside. When he leaves we go out and get them. This is a great service. ......and isn’t just for seniors.

take time to stock up, as you can see no one is going to save you, that is on you, dedicate a closet to stockpile your materials you may need over time.. learn all the ins and outs of survival materials and how to store them correctly...be prepared. Are you prepared? What if we lost power? And fresh water? How would you cook? With what? These are simple yet questions everyone should ask themselves... That earthquake is going to happen, that volcano will erupt, that hurricane will happen and if it doesn't a simple virus may be the thing that gets us all, if you prepared over time, well you wouldn't have so much stress... It is just common sense, and I hope everyone sees the value in doing this.
---As or these Costco returners, sure I would let them return at 1/3 the original cost, then unpack the individually wrapped packs and donate them to a local in need of organization. Then send the returner a cancellation notice along with a notice to Sam's club with their name so they know.

snippet.textDisplay: After renewing my membership in February I was unable to get what I needed delivered and when I went to the store there was always a line around the building. For someone like me that cannot stand for long periods of time this was not an option for me. Then I heard that they had hours specifically for the elderly and disabled but during those hours only the person on the membership was allowed in the store with claims that there would be someone to help me. I tried going on a few occasions during those times but once again there was a line around the store. Plus I did not see enough employees to help the customers individually. To make things worse is that the line was completely the opposite direction than disabled parking. Then once you finally would get through the line the carts were set up so that when you leave you once again have to go all the way in the other direction than the disabled parking. Costco claims that they are here for their customers during this crisis but I fail to see how.
